social_posts.post_text: Last show of tour tonight! So here’s me trying to stay awake 📸 @hartleyphoto
That’s a wrap on 2022. Thanks to everyone who came and shared a very unique experience for all of us and making it amazing.  Happy Holidays! 📸 @hartleyphoto
Happy Birthday @neilwestfall44 and happy holidays everyone. 📸 @hartleyphoto
Poland for the first time tomorrow! 📸 @hartleyphoto
Can’t believe we’ve never been to Poland before. Amazing 📸 @hartleyphoto

Want to take this moment to say thanks to our boys in @bringmethehorizon for bringing us on this tour. Every night’s been special, and there are no words for nights like tonight in Milan. 📸 @hartleyphoto
The person I’m pointing at through the phone is a lil bitch

SURPRISE! I’m out on tour with the boys in @newfoundglory for this leg of the Wet Hot All-American Summer tour. Playin some guitar with my boy @danfys holding down stage right. Come party 📸 @desotophoto

Big thank you to the @newfoundglory for trusting me to help out on their tour. Their hospitality and kindness was above and beyond. Some of the greatest people and a huge inspiration to me and millions across the planet no doubt. A true commitment to excellence. 
Their crew was amazing on many levels and it was an absolute pleasure. 
And @danfys holding it down night after night, he’s an absolute weapon. He knew their stuff inside and out like it was his own band. Can’t wait to see the future for @fouryearstrong ! Also don’t play card games with him that involve money. 
Again thanks to @elcapitan2phones @xchadballx @cyrusbolooki @psychosmoke, living legends

📸 @desotophoto

Check out this Silverburst Sparkle TL-2H for @kevineffinskaff  of @adtr 

This was a really fun build since we don’t do neck thru teles that often, so I did all of the body profile and contours by hand instead of programming them on the CNC. 

One of the most important specs on this build was the neck profile. After playing his American Series Soloist and really bonding with the speed neck shape, Kevin requested that the neck mimic his SL-3. 

I didn’t want to put it in the case and ship it, this thing rips!
